    <div class="content body-text">
        <h3>
      Age and Restrictions
    </h3>
        <p>
      At this time, KIC Events are open to adults, <strong>21 years of age or older</strong>. A registration MUST be filled out online
      AND be APPROVED PRIOR to arrival at the venue. Registrations must be completed by 8am the day of the party.
      There will be NO at the door registrations. Payment is not required at registration. Payment must be made prior
      to the event or at the door. A valid government issued ID is required for entrance to any event.
      <strong>NO ID = NO ENTRY; NO EXCEPTIONS.</strong>
    </p>
    <h3>
      Alcohol/Drug Policy
    </h3>
    <p>
      No alcohol, drugs, illegal substances and/or firearms may be brought to a KIC Event. Anyone who is noticeably
      affected by either alcohol or drugs will be refused admittance or asked to leave by Staff immediately.
    </p>
    <h3>
      Illegal Activities
    </h3>
    <p>
      Any activity illegal in the State of Ohio or the US is prohibited at KIC Events. This includes soliciting,
      prostituting, negotiating payment for play or sexual services, use or sale of substances, etc. Furthermore,
      there are no firearms or weapons intended to cause physical harm at events. KIC Events will not knowingly allow
      attendees to attend any function who have been convicted of a violent or sexual crime and/or is a registered 
      sex offender.
    </p>
    <h3>
      Dress Code/Attire/Clothing
    </h3>
    <p>
      KIC Events dress code will be specific to the venue and/or event hosting. Specific details will be posted in
      the event description.
    </p>
    <h3>
      Cameras/Cell Phones
    </h3>
    <p>
      At no time are pictures and/or videoing allowed by film, digital, cellphone, recording device, etc at a KIC
      Event. Cellphones are strongly encouraged to be left in your vehicle. If you have to have a cell phone on you,
      it is to be on vibrate and kept in a bag or pocket. If you need to make or respond to a call or text, use the
      posted designated areas to do so. Any person seen with a device may be ejected from the event.
    </p>
    <h3>
      Smoking/Vaping
    </h3>
    <p>
      Smoking and/or vaping is prohibited indoors at KIC Events. Smoking, including cigar play, is allowed in
      designated smoking areas dependent on venue.
    </p>
